$interpreted: Sophie: Who would've thought that Elio was carrying such a burden? It's no wonder that he looked so serious all the time. I shouldn't have bothered him...
Clark: It's not your fault. Elio helped me when I was at the Rune Academy.
Clark: To be honest, the Elio I know wouldn't disappear without first saying good-bye.
Sophie: But——
Clark: Maybe something happened to him. If that's the case...
Clark: Maria and I just can't seem to find a ferry to the Mechanical Territory. We have nothing to do...why don't we look for Elio together?
Sophie: Really!?
Maria: Processed! Maria can lend a hand!
Hanbei: ...Um. An actual hand? Maybe this is not what we need...
Clark: Did Elio leave anything behind? Did he say anything?
Rune: This stuff...was left behind...
Clark: Even though we shouldn't be looking at his personal belongings...
Clark: Huh? This map...
Clark: Wait. Let me change my glasses.
Clark: As expected. It's the Rune Academy's invisible ink.
Sophie: Invisible ink? What's that?
Clark: It's an ink that can only be seen by wearing special Rune glasses...
Clark: Maria, scan and project.
Maria: Maria is about to begin scanning. 5...4...3...
Ru-yi: Wah! Her eyes are lighting up...
Sophie: This is a map of New City. These dots are...
Clark: Hmm...for now I can't see why they're placed there.
Clark: Could be an important clue. We'll wait until the light of day to go find him.
Sophie: Rune, do you see something unusual over there?
Sophie: Based on Elio's map, these are the locations the dots indicate. There's another marker up ahead. Why don't we go to the Port and check it out?
Sanchez: Aya! Ahhh! Please! Help!!
Rune: San..chez?
Noble's Bodyguard: Where do ya think you're going! Beat that knucklehead!
Sanchez: *wince*...ohhhh, not good.
Sophie: Sanchez, are you okay? What happened? Who are those thugs?
Sanchez: *spit*...that noble hired me to move his luggage, then complained that my hand was dirty. Said that I marked up his bag, so he gave me a beating!
Sophie: That's a bit much! Some people are just heartless thugs!
Rune: Why do they bully Sanchez? We are...free.
Sanchez: Hmph. Nobody needs a reason to put others down. If people don't like your face, they'll find a way to put you down!
Sanchez: As long as I'm in this country, I'm nothing more than a slave...
Sanchez: So I've got to save up some money fast and get the hell out of this sh——
Sophie: ......
Sanchez: Forget it. What are you all doing out this way anyway?
Rune: We are looking for...Elio.
Sanchez: Elio? You're still looking for him?
Sophie: We found some clues on the map that Elio left behind.
Sanchez: Map? He...awwww, CRAP!
Sanchez: I just remembered I left some work unfinished. The boss is going to be pissed. I've got to run!
Sophie: Uh...good-bye, San——
